Skill Occupations List

The following is the current list of occupations with ANZSCO codes that are qualified to be nominated under the subclass 189 Independent Skilled Migrant visa. Note that this visa does not require a sponsoring employer, State or Territory.

For the Subclass 190 State/Territory Sponsored Skilled Migrant Visa, applicants may choose an occupation that is on this list, or one that is on the Consolidated Sponsored Occupations List (CSOL). Note, however, that not all States and Territories will sponsor all occupations, and there are often limits and quotas for occupations both at the State/Territory level and at the Federal level. For more information, consult your Registered Migration Agent for complete information.

Other transitional and special regulations may apply to the visa you are considering – consult your agent for more details.

  • Immigration Department SOL Website

This list was updated as of 1 July 2014.
